  "content": "<div><tt>Self-Mythologizing Fractal </tt></div>\n<div><tt><br></tt></div>\n<div><object><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; direction: ltr\">\n<tbody>\n<tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"border-style: solid; border-width: 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px; border-color: #ccc; padding: 3.0px 5.0px 3.0px 5.0px; min-width: 70px\"><br></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"border-style: solid; border-width: 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px 1.0px; border-color: #ccc; padding: 3.0px 5.0px 3.0px 5.0px; min-width: 70px\"><div><i>Yeah, Chris has been working with plays recently. He put on and was part of a South Florida play show where there was multiple short plays and he was, and I was also, we were all going to this like monthly event where people would write plays and then they'd read them aloud at this beer place and we'd be drinking and stuff and it'd be fun. And eventually they collected it all and they put the plays on in person. And Chris had a play and he also was the person who was anointed to write all of the integral pieces that connected all the plays, the voice between the plays. And he was also, you know, how could this apply to the Tombs of the Unknown Soldiers that he, it's not called that, but the manuscript he gave you, right? All of that stuff, right? Yes, yes, yes.</i></div>",
